\f1\b0\fs40 \cf2 Philosophy of the language\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf2 \
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Completeness\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 When it comes to decision making in the medical space it is important that all options are evaluated. If a script, for example, calculates the dose of a drug based on the bodyweight there should not be any gap or there must be a deliberate decision that all other possibilities are treated the same way.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf5 assess body weight:\
   0.5 kg ...  5.0 kg: ...\
   5.1 kg ... 10.0 kg: ...\
  10.1 kg ... 20.0 kg: ...\
  in all other cases: ...\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 \
The definition of body weight would look like this:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf5 "body weight" is a value:\
  valid units are kg, lbs.\
  valid values are between (0.5 kg ... 400 kg).\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Readability\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 Readability is one of the primary goals of the language. Therefore, no default values are used for any command. In principle each statements should be easy to understand in its context (plus/minus some lines). Here are some examples that help support that goal:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 Natural spelling
\f1\b0 . Currently no programming language exists that let programmers use spaces in either function or variable definitions or even let you you define whole sentences that have meaning. Once Hippocrates learned an expression, it can be used as in natural language (some limitations apply).\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 Example(s):\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf2 \ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 "Teaching" Hippocrates that the term "respiratory rate" is a value is as simple as this.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf5 "respiratory rate" is a value: ...\
