\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Meaningful\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 Values always come with a meaning. A meaning that determines healthy from not healthy for example or normal from not normal. And even the same value might have different meaning in a different context. The respiratory rate, for example, has plenty of normal ranges based on the age. Therefore Hippocrates lets you define the meaning of values. This allows physicians to write scripts without the need to know exact boundaries.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 Example:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone In the example below the respiratory rate (per minute) which is a value is complemented with meanings depending on the age (in years). In case the age is only 0 years the meaning is based on the pediatric age (in months).\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 "respiratory rate" is a value:\
  ...\
  meaning:\
    assess age:\
      0 years:\
        assess pediatric age:\
          0 months ... 2 months:\
            assess value:\
               0 ...  19: meaning = "critically low".\
              20 ...  29: meaning = "low".\
              30 ...  60: meaning = "normal".\
              61 ...  80: meaning = "high".\
              81 ... 100: meaning = "critically high".\
  ...\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 \
Beside the capability to define a meaning also a score can be defined. This can be used for discrete value that can be used for all kinds of assessments (like questionnaires). These score can be used to teach Hippocrates what answers represent a good value and which ones represent a bad value which is useful for statistical analysis.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 Example:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone The following example scores answers to pain levels, which can be used later on for statistical analysis.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\i0 \cf2 "pain level" is a value:\
  valid values:\
    value is ("No pain"; "Mild pain"; "Moderate pain";\
        "Severe pain": value = valid.\
...\
\
  scoring:\
    assess value:\
      no pain      : score = 0. score is best score.\
      mild pain    : score = 10.\
      moderate pain: score = 100.\
      severe pain  : score = 1000. score is worst score.\
  ...\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 Later in a plan this score can be used like that\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 ...\
diagnosis >\
  context >\
    timeframe is between (2 weeks ago ... now)!\
  assess trend of pain level:\
    getting worse: ...\
...\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 As an alternative a decision could be based on the majority of answers.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 ...\
diagnosis:\
  context >\
    timeframe is between (2 weeks ago ... now)!\
  assess majority of pain level:\
    severe pain: ...\
...\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Context\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 The syntax of Hippocrates is designed in a way that a statement always creates the context for subsequent statements.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 Example:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone A message creates the context for parameters that control the message. 
\f0\b show message
\f1\b0  creates the context for the following two lines. \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 show message to patient "This is a message for a patient":\
  message expires after 30 minutes.\
  color = red.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 \
Where this approach is not possible as the context creation contains more than one statement it can be created explicitly.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 Example:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \
There are more complex cases where the context can be created explicitly for a subsequent block. The following shows how a context for an analysis can be created. In this case\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 diagnosis:\
  context:\
    timeframe is between (2 weeks ago ... now)!\
    drug taken is yes!\
  assess majority of pain level:\
    severe pain:\
      assess count of drug taken:\
        0:\
...\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf10 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Separation\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 Separation is another primary design goal of Hippocrates. This separation comprises two domains. \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 Separation of technical domain
\f1\b0 . The language contains nothing that is specific to any platform the language is running on. Therefore no knowledge about technology is necessary.\
\

\f0\b Automatic handling of data. 
\f1\b0 All scripts that are created are created for a single person. Although the Hippocrates engine can deal with multiple plans and person the author of a script never has to cope with that complexity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Constraints\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 Constraints are another concept on Hippocrates. This means that every value must have a definition of valid values, which could also be a range or a set of ranges as well as discrete values. This eliminates to danger of assigning values that would lead to faulty and potential dangerous decisions.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 Values need to have a range
\f1\b0 . This range is used ensure that only meaningful and valid values are used at any time in the script.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 "body weight" is a number:\
  valid units:\
    valid units are (g; kg; lb).\
  valid values:\
    assess value:\
      0.5 kg ... 200.0 kg: value = valid.\
  ...\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0\b\fs36 \cf2 History\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 Keeping information about the history is an important principle of Hippocrates. Basically this has two meanings. Values that have been created in the past cannot be changed and values that are calculated will be stored with reference to values that have been used for calculation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf11 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Local\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 The Hippocrates language is designed to automatically translate scripts into supported local languages. Therefore each Hippocrates expression comes with pre-defined translations. Furthermore all text values can be complemented with translations.\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Medical\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 Hippocrates is focused on the medical domain and comes with a basic knowledge of medical terms. These terms can be used to associate values with anatomy or medicine. These terms will help implementing appropriate user interfaces.\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Persistent\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 Hippocrates automatically stores all changes to values. There is no need for the author of a script to take care of storing data.\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Autonomy\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 A plan is always complete. This means that any plan comes with all definitions that are required to execute the plan. Once the plan is deployed to Hippocrates engine it is analyzed and duplication is removed to save storage.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

