\f4\b0 \cf2 1 \\unit (1)\\ = \\formula\\\\unit (2)\\.\
1 \\unit (2)\\ = \\formula\\\\unit (1)\\.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf10 \ul \ulc10 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulc2 \
Rules:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone 1. Each 
\f0\b \\unit\\
\f1\b0  can be used only once.\
2. For each unit that should be converted into another unit a 
\f0\b \\conversion rule\\
\f1\b0  in both directions within the same 
\f0\b \\unit assessment paragraph\\
\f1\b0  must be defined.\
3. If no 
\f0\b \\conversion rule\\
\f1\b0  is defined all values that refer to each other must use the same unit.\
4. 
\f0\b \\unit handling\\
\f1\b0  is possible for 
\f0\b \\a number\\
\f1\b0  and 
\f0\b \\a time indications\\
\f1\b0 .\
5. If one or more units are specified for a 
\f0\b \\value\\
\f1\b0  one of these specified units must be used in the script next to the value.\
6. If the intended use of a \\value\\ is a concentration there must be a conversion rule between mmol/L and mg/dL defined.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

