\f4\b0 \cf2 \ulnone ...\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 \
\
However, units can also be converted into each other by providing formulas to achieve that.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 "glucose level" is a number >\
  valid units >\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2     \ul assess unit >\
\ulnone       \ul "mmol/L"; "mg/dL" >\ulnone \
        \ul unit is valid.\ulnone \
        \ul 1 mmol/L = 18.02 mg/dL.\ulnone \
        \ul 1 mg/dL = (1/18.02) mmol/dL. <<<\ulnone \
