\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Defining context\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 \
A context can be used to narrow down possibilities in a subsequent paragraph. This can either be on the timeline, a specific value group or a drug.\
\
At a high level a context is a construct that allows narrowing down of values for analytical purposes and to restrict access to data.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \{context\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 \\data context\\\
\\diagnosis context\\\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 \ul \ulc2 Rules:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone 1. If a 
\f2\i <question> 
\f1\i0 is used to create a context 
\f2\i for analysis
\f1\i0  must be specified,\
1. If any analytical method should be used 
\f2\i <context purpose>
\f1\i0  must be specified.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

