\f0\b \\context item\\
\f1\b0  cannot overlap.\
3. A context applies for all subsequent paragraphs in the paragraph it is defined.\
4. 
\f0\b \\timeframe is \\time scope\\\\ 
\f1\b0 only works in the past until 
\f0\b now
\f1\b0 . If the end point (e.g. defined by a date) is still in the future the context cannot be created and therefore  
\f0\b \{\{\\paragraph\\\}\}
\f1\b0  does not get executed.\
5. The  actually calculated time scope is based on the shortest period that fulfills all 
\f0\b \\time scope\\
\f1\b0  criteria. This could potentially end in no data in that period and would leave values that are calculated based on that timeframe as unknown.\
6. Contexts with \\
\f0\b timeframe is \\time scope\\\\ 
\f1\b0 can be nested as long as the timeframe in the inner context is within the timeframe of the outer context.\
7. If a \\filter context item\\ is not used in the
\f0\b  \\paragraph\\ 
\f1\b0 or any subsequent 
\f0\b \\paragraph\\ 
\f1\b0 it cannot be defined.\
