\f5\b \cf2 dispose \\message type\\.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 \
The information will be discarded and can only be found in the log of Hippocrates.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 resend \\message type\\ with next contact.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 \
Next time the same addressee receives an information the information will sent as well. The information will be sent in the order newest to oldest. This is the 
\f0\b default option
\f1\b0 .\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf10 \ul \ulc10 Discussion(s):\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf10 \ulnone 1. It needs to be defined how the exact protocol for mail delivery and using a Hippocrates ID will look like.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 Rules:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone 1. Either 
\f0\b dispose
\f1\b0  or 
\f0\b resend
\f1\b0  must be used in 
\f0\b \\paragraph\\
\f1\b0 .\
2. 
\f0\b within \\period of time\\
\f1\b0  can be used to limit the time for retrying to send the message. In case this option is used Hippocrates will use the full time to get confirmation that the contact channel was used successful.\
3. 
\f0\b after delivery
\f1\b0  can only be used if 
\f0\b send
\f1\b0  is used.\
4. send cannot be used for 
\f0\b \\addressee\\ patient
\f1\b0 .\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 Rules:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone 1. A 
\f0\b \\message paragraph\\
\f1\b0  can address the same 
\f0\b \\addressee\\ 
\f1\b0 only once.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf12 2. 
\f0\b \cf12 picture is \\picture path\\ 
\f1\b0 \cf12 can only be used if 
\f0\b \cf12 \\message type\\
\f1\b0 \cf12  is picture.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 3. Each 
\f0\b \\message type\\ expires... 
\f1\b0 expression can be used only once. However  
\f0\b \\duration\\
\f1\b0  and 
\f0\b \\event\\
\f1\b0  can be used together. Whatever comes first will trigger the expiration of the message.\
4. 
\f0\b maximum time to deliver message is \\period of time\\
\f1\b0 , 
\f0\b after delivery failure
\f1\b0  and 
\f0\b after delivery success
\f1\b0  cannot be used if the addressee is the 
\f0\b patient
\f1\b0 .\
5. 
\f0\b after delivery failure
\f1\b0  is called after all contact information have failed or the 
\f0\b maximum time to deliver message 
\f1\b0 has been exceeded.\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
