\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 Providing translations\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 \
Any script that is written in Hippocrates can be complemented with translations. Translations are a separate \\
\f0\b Hippocrates paragraph\\
\f1\b0  in a script.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf10 \ul \ulc10 Discussion:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf10 \ulnone 1. A message could also contain values. In this case the whole message block including the value has to be provided. This would also enable the possibility to choose the right unit depending on the target language and or country.\
2. In addition to point 1 it might be necessary that a geographic context can be established as this might trigger even more variants.\
3. Currently only western languages are specified. It needs to be decided which Asian languages should be included. It needs to be decided which non-Latin languages should be included.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \{Hippocrates translation paragraph\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 translations. >\
  languages. (\\supported languages\\).\
  \{\{\\translated text\\\}\}\
).\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \{specified languages\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 languages (\\language\\; \\language\\[\{\{; \\language\\\}\}]).\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \{language\}::
\f4\b0 \
English\
German\
French\
Spanish\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf12 Japanese\
Simplified Chinese\
Russian\
Hebrew\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf12 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \{translated text\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 (\\text in language 1\\; \\text in language 2\\...).\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \{text in language 1\}::\
\{text in language 2\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 \\message text\\\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\i0\b \cf12 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 \ul \ulc2 Rules:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone 1. Translations must be provided in 
\f0\b \\translated text\\ 
\f1\b0 the same order as the languages are specified in 
\f0\b languages
\f1\b0 .\
2. Messages that are translated must be provided including any 
\f0\b \\value\\
\f1\b0  used in the source language and the target language(s).\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 \
\
Example(s):\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \
At any position within a Hippocrates plan a translation paragraph can be included.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 translations >\
  languages (English; German).\
  ("This is an English text"; "Das ist ein deutscher Text").\
<\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 Also more complex translations can be provided. The following examples shows the translation of an information that also contains values.  In addition to the text the name of the value also needs to be translated.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\i0 \cf2 ...\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \ul \ulc2 send message to physician
\f4\b0 \ulnone  \
  "The inhaler has been used " count of inhaler used \'84in\
    past 7 days".\
...\
\
translations >\
  languages (English; German).\
  ("inhaler used"; "Inhalator verwendet").\
  ("The inhaler has been used " count of inhaler used \'84in\
    past 7 days"; "Der Inhalator wurde in den letzten 7 Tagen " \
    Anzahl von Inhalator verwendet " verwendet.").\
<\
\
\
