\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Definition of custom events\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 \
Hippocrates also supports the definition of custom events. The feature of definition of semantic meanings can be used define any expression to require, trigger and catch events. This definition must be placed outside the plan paragraph in a script.
\f2\i \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\i0\b \cf2 \{custom event\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 \\name of event\\ is an event >\
  \\request phrase\\\
  \\trigger phrase\\\
  \\catch phrase\\\
).\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \{request phrase\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 request event is \\text\\.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 Defines the sentence that is used to request use of trigger phrase.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \{trigger phrase\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 trigger event is \\text\\.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 Defines the sentence that is actually triggering the event.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \
\{catch phrase\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 catch event is \\text\\.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 Defines the phrase that finally catches the event. The phrase must be used in combination with after (
\f0\b after \\catch phrase\\
\f1\b0 ).\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 \
\
Example:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \
The following example shows the use of custom events for a first dose administration.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 "first dose" is an event >\
  
\f5\b \cf14 request event is "drug requires first dose\
    administration".\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2   \cf7 trigger event is "first dose has been administrated".\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2   
\f5\b \cf15 catch event is "first dose has been administrated".\

\f4\b0 \cf2 <\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

