Returns the text description of the device that was used to generate the value. It is simply a text. This text can be compared inside the the script against e.g. validated device the value should be coming from. This validation can be placed in the validation section of a value.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 Example(s):\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone In the following example some very specific validation criteria are added in the validation section of  a value. Only if these criteria apply Hippocrates would accept the data that is provided via an API call. This functionality could be used in clinical trial setting where the source of data should be limited to validated / accepted sources.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

