\f0\i0\b\fs32 \cf2 Intended use (required)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 \
Intended use helps to define constraints on how the value can be used in scripts. Within this paragraph it can be controlled what actions can be taken with a value.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf16 \ul \ulc16 Caution:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf16 \ulnone 1. Changing any intended use settings might invalidate parts or all of the scripts if the intended use rules become violated.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \{intended use paragraph\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

