\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 Question\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 In many cases a value needs to be acquired by asking a person. This question can be embedded in the definition of a value to make the actual script more readable.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\b \cf2 \{question paragraph\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\b0 \cf2 question >\
  ask "Question text" [>\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\i0 \cf2     \\answer assessor\\\
    [\{\{\\question option\\\}\}]<]\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 <\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\i0 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 \ul \ulc2 Rules:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone 1. If 
\f0\b \\answer assessor\\
\f1\b0  is not used, the possible answers will be constructed from 
\f0\b \\valid values paragraph\\
\f1\b0 .\
2. If 
\f0\b \\answer assessor\\ 
\f1\b0 is defined the full valid range specified in 
\f0\b \\valid values paragraph\\ 
\f1\b0 needs to be covered.\
\
In 
\f0\b \\question paragraph\\
\f2\i\b0  
\f1\i0 an addition phrase is available:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 in case confidence of answer is \\confidence range\\ > ... <\
for all other values of confidence of answer > ... <\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 \
With that sentence an action depending on the confidence of the answer can be triggered.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 Rules:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone 1. To evaluate the confidence value 
\f0\b \\confidence paragraph\\ 
\f1\b0 must be defined.\
2. 
\f0\b in case confidence of answer
\f1\b0  can be used multiple times, as long as 
\f0\b \\confidence range\\
\f1\b0  does not overlap.\
3. If used 
\f0\b \\confidence range\\
\f1\b0  ranges do not cover the range 
\f0\b 0% ... 100%
\f1\b0  the expression 
\f0\b for all other values of confidence of answer
\f1\b0  must be used. \
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 Example(s):\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \
To be written (for the moment see "Raising questions").\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 "age" is a number >\
  valid units >\
    assess unit > year > unit is valid. <<<\
  valid values >\
    assess value >\
      0 years ... 150 years > value is valid. <<<\
  ...\
  confidence >\
    assess value >\
        0 years ...  99 years > confidence of value = 100%. <\
      100 years ... 150 years > confidence of value = 80%. <<<\
  ...\
\
  question >\
    ask "What is your age in years?" >\
      in case confidence of answer is between (0% ... 79%) >\
        validate answer once >\
          before first validation >\
            show message to patient "Please confirm your age." <<<\
      for all other values of confidence of value > no action. <<\
<\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

