\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 Calculation\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 \
An alternative way to acquiring a value through a question is calculating it. Hippocrates determines each time the value is accessed if the value needs to be calculated. In case other values are necessary for that calculation Hippocrates "follows" the chain of values that are needed and triggers the required actions (which could be calculation other values or raising questions).\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \{calculation paragraph\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 calculation >\
  [\\decision\\ >]\
      value = <Rvalue>. [<]\
<\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 \ul \ulc2 Rules:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone 1. 
\f0\b value = \\Rvalue\\ 
\f1\b0 must be the innermost expression.\
2. Any control structure that is used cannot be ambiguous allowing to reach 
\f0\b value = \\Rvalue\\
\f1\b0  multiple times (e.g. having a default calculation at the top of the paragraph and overriding that in a later statement based on a decision.\
3. Only valid values can be assigned. If a 
\f0\b \\formula\\
\f1\b0  is used Hippocrates will pre-evaluate the formula to determine if min and max values are within the specified range of 
\f0\b \\value\\
\f1\b0 .\
4. The confidence of the value is set to the lowest confidence of any value used (weakest link in the chain) in the calculation or any decision used before reaching the assignment 
\f0\b value = \\Rvalue\\
\f1\b0 .\
5.The calculation is only executed, if\
a. the value is 
\f0\b unknown
\f1\b0 .
\f0\b  
\f1\b0 \
b. the reuse period has been expired \
c. the required confidence level of the current value is not sufficient\
d. any value that is used in the calculation has been changed\
6. 
\f0\b \\value\\
\f1\b0  with 
\f0\b \\calculation paragraph\\
\f1\b0  cannot be used as 
\f0\b \\Lvalue\\
\f1\b0 .\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 Example(s):\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \
The example shows the calculation of the body mass index (
\f0\b BMI
\f1\b0 ). This is straight forward. What is more complex. In the example the it will be checked at compile time what the extreme values of the formula can be based on the input values 
\f0\b height
\f1\b0  and 
\f0\b body weight
\f1\b0 .\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 "BMI" is a number >\
  valid units >\
    assess unit >\
      "kg/m^2" > unit is valid. <<<\
  valid values >\
    assess value >\
      0 kg/m^2 ... (400 kg)/(2.5 m)^2 > value is valid. <<<\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2   \ul calculation >\
\ulnone     \ul value = (height in m) / (body weight in kg)^2. <\ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 <\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 Confidence\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 \
Value in Hippocrates all comes with a confidence value that changes over time. Confidence control is intended to be used if decisions require a high confidence in the values involved in the decisions.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \{confidence paragraph\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 confidence >\
  [\\decision\\ >]\
    confidence of value = \\percentage100\\. [<]\
<\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 \ul \ulc2 Rules:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone 1.
\f0\b  confidence of value = \\percentage100\\ 
\f1\b0 must be the innermost sentence.\
2.
\f0\b  confidence of value = \\percentage100\\ 
\f1\b0 cannot be called more than once in the same path.\
3. If 
\f0\b \\confidence paragraph\\
\f2\i\b0  
\f1\i0 is not specified a confidence of 100% is assumed.\
4. The 
\f0\b \\confidence paragraph\\
\f1\b0  will also be used to assess the confidence of an answer with
\f2\i  
\f0\i0\b \\question paragraph\\
\f1\b0 .\
5. The actual confidence of the value is calculated as 
\f0\b confidence of value
\f1\b0  minus the decline of confidence as defined in 
\f0\b \\reuse paragraph\\
\f1\b0 .\
6. 
\f0\b \\confidence paragraph\\
\f2\i\b0  
\f1\i0 can only be used if 
\f0\b \\calculation paragraph\\
\f1\b0  is present. For 
\f0\b \\calculation paragraph\\
\f1\b0  the confidence is based on the values that are used in the calculation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0\b\fs32 \cf2 Reuse\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf2 \
Hippocrates can restrict the use of values to a certain period of time. If the value is used after that period Hippocrates will raise questions to acquire these values again.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\b \cf2 \{reuse paragraph\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 reuse >\
  [\\decision\\ >]\
    \\reuse\\ [<]\
<.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\i0\b \cf2 \{reuse\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 reuse period of value is \\period of time\\ [with \
  \\percentage100\\ linear decline of confidence].\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 \ul \ulc2 Rules:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone 1. 
\f0\b \\reuse definition\\
\f1\b0  must be the innermost sentence.\
2. Any control structure that is used cannot be ambiguous allowing to reach 
\f0\b \\reuse definition\\
\f1\b0  multiple times at the same time.\
3. If 
\f0\b \\reuse paragraph\\
\f2\i\b0  
\f1\i0 is not specified an infinite reuse period is assumed.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 \
Example(s):\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone \
A simple example is weight where the reuse time could depend from the age.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 "weight" is a number >\
  ...\
  reuse >\
    assess age >\
      0 years ... 1 year >\
        reuse period of value is 2 weeks with 30% linear decline\
          of confidence.\
      2 years ... 10 years > ... <\
      in all other cases >\
        reuse period of value is 6 months with 20% linear decline\
          of confidence. <<<\
<\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf2 Alternative style\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf2 \
reuse >\
  in case age is between (0 years ... 1 year) >\
    reuse period of value is 2 weeks with 30% linear decline\
      of confidence. <\
  in case age is between (2 years ... 10 years) > ... <\
  for all other values of age >\
    reuse period of value is 6 months with 20% linear decline\
      of confidence. <\
<\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

