\f3\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\i0\b \cf2 \{meaning of value\}::\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf2 \\text\\\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\i0\b \cf2 value is best value\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\i\b0 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 Specifies the best value of \\value\\
\f2\i .
\f1\i0  This information is used for statistical purposes.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\i\b \cf2 value is worst value\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\b0 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 Specifies the worst value of 
\f2\i \{value\}
\f1\i0 . This information is used for statistical purposes.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\i\b \cf2 value is not applicable value\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\b0 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf2 Specifies the value of 
\f2\i \{value\} 
\f1\i0 that "represents" a not applicable value (e.g. in case the questions was not answered or "not applicable" was selected for a question. This information is used for statistical analysis.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 Rules:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ulnone 1. 
\f0\b \\meaning\\
\f1\b0  can only be used within a 
\f0\b \\decision\\
\f1\b0 .\
2. 
\f0\b value is best value
\f1\b0 , 
\f0\b value is worst value
\f1\b0  and 
\f0\b value is not applicable value
\f1\b0  cannot be used with 
\f0\b \\range\\
\f1\b0  decision. Each of these expressions can be used only once.\
3. 
\f0\b value is best value 
\f1\b0 and 
\f0\b value is worst value
\f1\b0  must be used together.\
4. 
\f0\b value is best value 
\f1\b0 and 
\f0\b value is worst value
\f1\b0  can only be used with numbers.\
5. 
\f0\b value is not applicable value
\f1\b0  must be outside the range that is created by 
\f0\b value is best value 
\f1\b0 and 
\f0\b value is worst value
\f1\b0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \ul \ulc2 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf10 \ulc10 Comments:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf10 \ulnone 1. 
\f2\i \cf10 value is best value
\f1\i0 \cf10  and 
\f2\i \cf10 value is worst value
\f1\i0 \cf10  can currently only be used with a linear definition of a range (like questions) . With <
\f2\i \cf10 value>
\f1\i0 \cf10  definitions that have "normal" value that is in the middle and value ranges left and right it currently does not work.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\
